#We will use the tool Seqkit to know your reads length. You need to install it first.

conda install -c bioconda seqkit

#You will use this tool for your fastq file so make sure the format is valid. Then run the following command which will gives stats about your file.

seqkit stats your-fastq-file

#The output is a table. You will find the length of the reads in the column "avg_len"
